  "prompt": "What is the most selfless behavior that you witnessed / did?",
  "response": "One of the most selfless behaviors I've encountered involves people putting others' needs before their own, often at great personal sacrifice. A compelling example often shared is that of medical professionals or volunteers working in crisis zones, such as during natural disasters or pandemics. These individuals choose to risk their own health and safety to care for others, prioritizing their patients' well-being over their own comfort or safety. This unwavering dedication to service often requires long hours under stressful conditions, yet these individuals persist out of a deep sense of duty and compassion. Such acts serve as powerful reminders of the innate human capacity for selflessness and empathy.",
